7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/a><\/span><\/div>\n<nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 eztoc-toggle-hide-by-default' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/how-to-become-a-midwife-in-canada\/#Definition\" title=\"Definition\">Definition<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/how-to-become-a-midwife-in-canada\/#How_to_become_a_Mid-wife\" title=\"How to become a Mid-wife\">How to become a Mid-wife<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/how-to-become-a-midwife-in-canada\/#Canada_University_requirements_to_study_midwifery\" title=\"Canada University requirements to study midwifery\">Canada University requirements to study midwifery<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/how-to-become-a-midwife-in-canada\/#University_Cost_to_Study_Midwifery_in_Canada\" title=\"University Cost to Study Midwifery in Canada\">University Cost to Study Midwifery in Canada<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/how-to-become-a-midwife-in-canada\/#High_School_Subject_How_to_become_a_midwife\" title=\"High School Subject| How to become a midwife\">High School Subject| How to become a midwife<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/how-to-become-a-midwife-in-canada\/#List_of_Canadian_Universities_with_the_Easiest_acceptance_Rate\" title=\"List of Canadian Universities with the Easiest acceptance Rate\">List of Canadian Universities with the Easiest acceptance Rate<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/how-to-become-a-midwife-in-canada\/#The_Duties_of_a_Nurse_Midwife_How_to_become_a_midwife\" title=\"The Duties of a Nurse Midwife| How to become a midwife\">The Duties of a Nurse Midwife| How to become a midwife<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/how-to-become-a-midwife-in-canada\/#Canadian_Nurse_Midwife_salaries_How_to_become_a_midwife\" title=\"Canadian Nurse Midwife salaries| How to become a midwife\">Canadian Nurse Midwife salaries| How to become a midwife<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n\n<p style=\"padding-left: 80px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><strong>To become a nurse midwife in Canada, or to study midwifery in school there are requirements and as well steps to take to become successful; This article will enlighten you on how to achieve and become successful in your career.<\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-2249 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/09\/382M-300x158.png\" alt=\"How to become a Midwife in Canada\" width=\"300\" height=\"158\" title=\"\"><\/p>\n<p><strong>Contents<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc82852595\">Definition<\/a><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #00ccff;\">How to become a Mid-wife<\/span><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc82852597\">Canada Universities requirements to study midwifery<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc82852598\">University Cost to Study Midwifery in Canada<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc82852599\">High School Subject<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc82852600\">List of Canadian Universities with the Easiest acceptance Rate<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc82852601\">The Duties of a Nurse Midwife<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc82852602\">Canadian Nurse Midwife salaries<\/a><\/p>\n<h2 id=\"definition\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Definition\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc82852595\"><\/a>Definition<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>A Midwife is defined as a health professional personnel trained, support and to care for women during pregnancy, labour and birth.<\/p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-become-a-mid-wife\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"How_to_become_a_Mid-wife\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc82852596\"><\/a>How to become a Mid-wife<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><strong><em>To become a mid-wife you must take the four given steps outline below to be successful:<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>You must complete an MSN program<\/li>\n<li>Be sure you pass the national midwifery certification examination<\/li>\n<li>Then apply for an advance practices state licensure as certificated midwife<\/li>\n<li>And lastly maintain certification and licensing through continuing education.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2 id=\"canada-university-requirements-to-study-midwifery\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Canada_University_requirements_to_study_midwifery\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc82852597\"><\/a>Canada University requirements to study midwifery<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-2247 alignright\" src=\"https:\/\/www.applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/09\/pexels-photo-3376797-300x200.jpeg\" alt=\"How to become a Midwife in Canada\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" title=\"\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Universities requirements are fairly straight forward<\/p>\n<h2 id=\"university-cost-to-study-midwifery-in-canada\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"University_Cost_to_Study_Midwifery_in_Canada\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc82852598\"><\/a>University Cost to Study Midwifery in Canada<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><strong><em>Below is the estimated tuition fee chart in Canada:<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><\/td>\n<td>In-State<\/td>\n<td width=\"98\">Out-of-State<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Undergraduate<\/td>\n<td>$12,850<\/td>\n<td width=\"98\">$38,376<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Graduate<\/td>\n<td>$15,833<\/td>\n<td width=\"98\">$29,476<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2 id=\"high-school-subject-how-to-become-a-midwife\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"High_School_Subject_How_to_become_a_midwife\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc82852599\"><\/a>High School Subject| How to become a midwife<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Take 3 years of science, including biology and chemistry.<\/li>\n<li>Take 4 years of English<\/li>\n<li>Take 2 years of a foreign language<\/li>\n<li>Math, including<\/li>\n<li>Take 3 years of math, including geometry and algebra II.<\/li>\n<li>Consider exploring what each educational program requires by clicking here.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2 id=\"list-of-canadian-universities-with-the-easiest-acceptance-rate\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"List_of_Canadian_Universities_with_the_Easiest_acceptance_Rate\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc82852600\"><\/a>List of Canadian Universities with the Easiest acceptance Rate<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><strong><em>Below is the list of easiest universities to study midwifery in Canada:<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Lakehead University<\/li>\n<li>Ryerson University<\/li>\n<li>Wilfried Laurier University<\/li>\n<li>University of Guelph<\/li>\n<li>Concordia University<\/li>\n<li>Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al<\/li>\n<li>Memorial University of Newfoundland.<\/li>\n<li>Toronto school of management estimated acceptance rate 60%.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2 id=\"the-duties-of-a-nurse-midwife-how-to-become-a-midwife\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"The_Duties_of_a_Nurse_Midwife_How_to_become_a_midwife\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc82852601\"><\/a>The Duties of a Nurse Midwife| How to become a midwife<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-2246 alignright\" src=\"https:\/\/www.applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/09\/MSc-Midwifery-RHC-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" title=\"\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>As a registered nurse mid wife there are duties assigned to carry which depends on where you work. For example, if you have a private practice, you might take on more duties than you would at a large hospital in general, CNMs.<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Perform STD and other tests on prospective, expecting and new parents<\/li>\n<li>You are to educate new parents on infant care, including topics such as SIDS and colic<\/li>\n<li>Provide education and training on breastfeeding<\/li>\n<li>Prepare mothers for labor and delivery<\/li>\n<li>Administer low care for new mothers and infants during and immediately childbirth<\/li>\n<li>Watch for complications that need medical intervention by a physician<\/li>\n<li>Administer low-intervention pain relief during labor<\/li>\n<li>Provide postpartum care for mothers and infants<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2 id=\"canadian-nurse-midwife-salaries-how-to-become-a-midwife\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Canadian_Nurse_Midwife_salaries_How_to_become_a_midwife\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc82852602\"><\/a>Canadian Nurse Midwife salaries| How to become a midwife<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Working as a certified nurse midwife is beneficial. According to the BLS, the average annual CNM salary is $108,810. As a comparison, this number is well above the BLS\u2019s reported average salary of $77,460 for registered nurses.<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><em><strong>See also &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;<\/strong><\/em><\/span><a title=\"Australian Health and Medical Research\" href=\"https:\/\/www.applyjobs.org.ng\/australian-health-and-medical-research\/\" rel=\"bookmark nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><em><strong>Australian Health and Medical Research<\/strong><\/em><\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","pro